tiaraV35Mib.name: tiaraV35Mib
tiaraV35Mib.contactinfo: Tiara Networks Customer Support 525 Race Street, Suite 100, San Jose, CA 95126 USA Tel: +1 408-216-4700 Fax: +1 408-216-4701 Email: support@tiaranetworks.com
tiaraV35Mib.description: MIB definitions for Tiara V35 module.

v35ConfigTable.name: v35ConfigTable
v35ConfigTable.description: Tiara Networks V35 interface-related configurable parameters are listed in this table.

v35IfIndex.name: v35IfIndex
v35IfIndex.description: An integer value that is an index in the entries of the ifTable (MIB-II) with a V.35 interface type.

v35ConfigClockRate.name: v35ConfigClockRate
v35ConfigClockRate.description: Configures the clock rate for V35.

v35ConfigClockSource.name: v35ConfigClockSource
v35ConfigClockSource.description: Configures the clock source for V35. It can be either internal or line.

v35ConfigMode.name: v35ConfigMode
v35ConfigMode.description: Configures the mode for V35 to be either dce or dte.

v35ConfigCRC.name: v35ConfigCRC
v35ConfigCRC.description: Configures the cyclic redundancy check for V35 to be either 16 or 32 bits.

v35ConfigDataMode.name: v35ConfigDataMode
v35ConfigDataMode.description: Configures the data for V.35 to be either normal or inverted.

v35ConfigFlowControl.name: v35ConfigFlowControl
v35ConfigFlowControl.description: Configures the hardware flow control for V.35 to be either on or off.

v35StatsTable.name: v35StatsTable
v35StatsTable.description: Tiara Networks V35 interface-related status variables are listed in this table.

v35StatsAlarmStatus.name: v35StatsAlarmStatus
v35StatsAlarmStatus.description: Specifies the status of the V35 alarm. If the bit is set, it indicates that the alarm state is on. Alarm bits are mode dependent; they are interpreted as follows: v35-alarms-DTR - DTR not received from DTE (V.35 is DCE) v35-alarms-DSR - DSR not received from DCE (V.35 is DTE) v35-alarms-ST - V.35 adaptor driving ST (V.35 is DCE) v35-alarms-CTS - CTS not received from DCE (V.35 is DTE) v35-alarms-RTS - RTS not received from DTE (V.35 is DCE)

v35StatsFramesIn.name: v35StatsFramesIn
v35StatsFramesIn.description: Specifies the number of incoming frames.

v35StatsFramesOut.name: v35StatsFramesOut
v35StatsFramesOut.description: Specifies the number of outgoing frames.

v35StatsOctetsIn.name: v35StatsOctetsIn
v35StatsOctetsIn.description: Specifies the number of incoming octets.

v35StatsOctetsOut.name: v35StatsOctetsOut
v35StatsOctetsOut.description: Specifies the number of outgoing octets.

v35StatsCRCErrors.name: v35StatsCRCErrors
v35StatsCRCErrors.description: Specifies the number of CRC errors that have been identified so far.

v35SlotNumber.name: v35SlotNumber
v35SlotNumber.description: This V35 trap variable specifies the slot number of the V35 interface.

v35AlarmType.name: v35AlarmType
v35AlarmType.description: This V35 alarm type specifies the type of the alarm trap generated by the agent for the V35 interface. Alarm bits are mode dependent; they are interpreted as follows: v35-alarms-DTR - DTR not received from DTE (V.35 is DCE) v35-alarms-DSR - DSR not received from DCE (V.35 is DTE) v35-alarms-ST - V.35 adaptor driving ST (V.35 is DCE) v35-alarms-CTS - CTS not received from DCE (V.35 is DTE) v35-alarms-RTS - RTS not received from DTE (V.35 is DCE)

v35AlarmOnTrap.name: v35AlarmOnTrap
v35AlarmOnTrap.description: V35 alarm traps for the Alarm On state.

v35AlarmOffTrap.name: v35AlarmOffTrap
v35AlarmOffTrap.description: V35 alarm traps for the Alarm Off state.
